And it wasn't just the children having fun - the lure of the brown sludge was too 
much for some parents and they also got stuck into getting muddy, 
although they had to join the youngsters at the end to be hosed down by a firetruck.

Candi Bostain was one of the adult participants who took part.

She said: ‘There’s nothing like the mud squishing between your toes. Now I know what pigs feel like.’

