Mud Day 2012 also doubled up as a training exercise for Western Wayne Hazardous Materials 
Response Team, which includes firefighters from Farmington Hills and 22 
other metro Detroit departments.

Farmington Hills Fire Lt. Mike Kish. 
told Farmington Hills Patch that no other hazmat team in the country does
a live decontamination exercise.

'We set the whole thing up in about 12 minutes,' he said.

Children
moved through a line of firefighters who hosed the mud off them, 
although some younger children were held up to hosed down by their 
parents.

'In real life, there would be soap and water,' Mr Kish added.

